# Hashtag Frequency

df %>% 
  unnest_tokens(output = hashtag, input = text, token = "tweets") %>%
  filter(!hashtag %in% c("#boostershot",'#booster'), str_detect(hashtag, "^#")) %>%
  count(hashtag, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(5) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = reorder(hashtag, n)))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(x = 'Frequency', y = '',  title = 'Hashtag Frequency', 
       caption = '"covid19" is the most widely used hastag in this dataset.')

  head(100)

  unnest_tokens(output = hashtag, input = text, token = "tweets") %>%

df %>%
    unnest_tokens(input = text, output = word) %>% 
    anti_join(get_stopwords()) %>% 
    count( word, sort = TRUE) %>%
    inner_join(get_sentiments("afinn")) %>%
    mutate(sentiment = value) %>% 
    filter(!is.na(sentiment)) %>%
    count(sentiment, sort = TRUE) %>% 
    mutate(n = n/sum(n)) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(sentiment, n))+geom_col(position = 'dodge')+
    labs(y='Relative Frequency', x ='', title = "Distribution of Sentiment in the #boostershot Text Data", caption='The sentiment seems to be pretty normally distributed.')

df %>%

# Hashtag Frequency

df %>% 
  unnest_tokens(output = hashtag, input = text, token = "tweets") %>%
  filter(!hashtag %in% c("#humanrightsday"), str_detect(hashtag, "^#")) %>%

  head(5) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = reorder(hashtag, n)))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(x = 'Frequency', y = '',  title = 'Hashtag Frequency', 
       caption = 'The most frequent hashtag, "justice for Tigray" is speaking out for the justice of sexual assault \n crimes that government-affiliated people in Ethiopia have committed.')

# word frequency
